#: ../../user/how-to-guides/backup-emergency-restore-v3.rst:3
#: 248851373ac6444faafbbeba627afcc6
msgid "Emergency backup recovery (v3)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/backup-emergency-restore-v3.rst:6
#: d2da042ab3cc431b96e7364c3c6e5b5e
msgid "This page describes how to perform an emergency restore of a backup created on Qubes R2 or later (which uses backup format version 3)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/backup-emergency-restore-v3.rst:8
#: 2fdc7e89e2d445bba2eaa951444b42ec
msgid "The Qubes backup system has been designed with emergency disaster recovery in mind. No special Qubes-specific tools are required to access data backed up by Qubes. In the event a Qubes system is unavailable, you can access your data on any GNU/Linux system with the following procedure."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/backup-emergency-restore-v3.rst:10
#: f78a013a362649c6a6299abb5ad5d42c
msgid "**Note:** In the following example, the backup file is both *encrypted* and *compressed*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/backup-emergency-restore-v3.rst:12
#: bf446ceac8a049839ccf671c1098e272
msgid "Untar the main backup file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/backup-emergency-restore-v3.rst:34
#: 28f0938dbeb34ddc942c592c2df70bfb
msgid "Set the backup passphrase environment variable. While this isn’t strictly required, it will be handy later and will avoid saving the passphrase in the shell’s history."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/backup-emergency-restore-v3.rst:42
#: 4bcc8851832b41bc96026e55023e5de4
msgid "Verify the integrity of the ``backup-header`` file, which contains basic information about your backup."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/backup-emergency-restore-v3.rst:53
#: ../../user/how-to-guides/backup-emergency-restore-v3.rst:86
#: 562f8f17870d426796202977ffd23ee4
#: 0e0ce4d5fa554ba6976a4aa91c8181c1
msgid "**Note:** The hash values should match. If they do not match, then the backup file may have been tampered with, or there may have been a storage error."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/backup-emergency-restore-v3.rst:55
#: cd0437dbb318417a853479a31068dad6
msgid "**Note:** If your backup was hashed with a message digest algorithm other than ``sha512``, you must substitute the correct message digest command. This information is contained in the ``backup-header`` file (see step 4), however it is not recommended to open this file until its integrity and authenticity has been verified (the current step). A complete list of supported message digest algorithms can be found with ``openssl list-message-digest-algorithms``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/backup-emergency-restore-v3.rst:59
#: c74acd03878d4333b4b644bf80a42438
msgid "Read the ``backup-header``. You’ll need some of this information later. The file will look similar to this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/backup-emergency-restore-v3.rst:72
#: 2e1fd4833e724907a47bf3632e954491
msgid "**Note:** If you see ``version=2`` here, go to :doc:`Emergency Backup Recovery - format version 2 </user/how-to-guides/backup-emergency-restore-v2>` instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/backup-emergency-restore-v3.rst:74
#: 9f5427499bc14732befeb6042e5074ff
msgid "Verify the integrity of the ``private.img`` file which houses your data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/backup-emergency-restore-v3.rst:88
#: 14c7b080844443e48b841bcfb77d581c
msgid "**Note:** If your backup was hashed with a message digest algorithm other than ``sha512``, you must substitute the correct message digest command. This information is contained in the ``backup-header`` file (see step 4). A complete list of supported message digest algorithms can be found with ``openssl list-message-digest-algorithms``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/backup-emergency-restore-v3.rst:92
#: ebe7dd7ba1b74d8c8b29b0f41f6d1e5e
msgid "Decrypt the ``private.img`` file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/backup-emergency-restore-v3.rst:99
#: 7421375e610340a682969e68c99d02f6
msgid "**Note:** If your backup was encrypted with a cipher algorithm other than ``aes-256-cbc``, you must substitute the correct cipher command. This information is contained in the ``backup-header`` file (see step 4). A complete list of supported cipher algorithms can be found with ``openssl list-cipher-algorithms``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/backup-emergency-restore-v3.rst:101
#: 036b5fe09bbd4038b07ad0083882df7f
msgid "Decompress the decrypted ``private.img`` file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/backup-emergency-restore-v3.rst:110
#: 1d9cefe4e15e477fb5a0f28de9e0090c
msgid "**Note:** If your backup was compressed with a program other than ``gzip``, you must substitute the correct compression program. This information is contained in the ``backup-header`` file (see step 4). For example, if you used ``bzip2``, then you should do this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/backup-emergency-restore-v3.rst:119
#: 10aa626944d7430192c146a34183d45f
msgid "Untar the decrypted and decompressed ``private.img`` file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/backup-emergency-restore-v3.rst:128
#: 39af000d5fdc4fcf87b7a9c292a7e0fb
msgid "Mount the private.img file and access your data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/backup-emergency-restore-v3.rst:139
#: 6700bcb743874e4db374261e9067d37b
msgid "Success! If you wish to recover data from more than one VM in your backup, simply repeat steps 5–9 for each additional VM."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/backup-emergency-restore-v3.rst:141
#: c5711279537143adad34505ccec1e13a
msgid "**Note:** You may wish to store a copy of these instructions with your Qubes backups in the event that you fail to recall the above procedure while this web page is inaccessible. All Qubes documentation, including this page, is available in plain text format in the following Git repository: https://github.com/QubesOS/qubes-doc.git"
msgstr ""
